docstring.long_description:
Calculated element-wise for a Vector or OrderedPair input.

Use log_base "input" to use the bottom input as the base.
docstring.short_description: Find the logarithm of input a with base b.

parameters.name: a
parameters.description: The input a use to compute the log of a.

parameters.name: b
parameters.description: The input b use to compute the log with base b.

parameters.name: log_base
parameters.description: The base to use for the logarithm, by default "e".

returns.description:
OrderedPair if a is an OrderedPair.
x: the x-axis of input a.
y: the result of the logarithm.

Scalar if a is a Scalar.
c: the result of the logarithm.

Vector if a is a Vector.
v: the result of the logarithm.
